	body 
		h1.typl8-alpha Base Type
		p This is what an ordinary, unadorned paragraph looks like.  Pretty uninteresting really.  Although it does bear noting the default font-size and line-height.  Also see what happens with word-breaks and hyphenation.  Actually, it's not that <em>uninteresting</em> after all!  There's also the matter of default 'color', which I believe is not full black.  More something like #444 or #222 I believe.  There's also the choice of serifed or non-serifed font for the base.
		p Personally, I find the page eminently readable.  Not so much for the content but rather the easy flow of typ across the page.  The result is easy on the eye too with regard to the choice of background &amp; foreground colors.
		p Note also the default use of <strong>indents</strong> on paragraph text after the 1st paragraph.  Note something I expected!
		h1.typl8-alpha Some slightly more advanced type...
		p Let's look at for example, <abbr>small caps</abbr>, what are <em>they</em> all about?  These can be accessed through the '&#60;abbr&#62;' tag.
		
